The paper discusses the comparison and analysis of three serverless orchestration systems, which are related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.Distributed Systems). The paper also discusses the programming and billing models, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper evaluates the run-time overhead of different infrastructures, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
